            "heading": "Snore no more",
            "body": "<p>Snoring starts in a blocked nose. Air can't get through, your mouth falls open, and the soft tissue behind it starts to rattle. The band holds your nose open, so your mouth stays shut and the noise never begins. In a 14-night trial of nasal strips, partners rated the snoring quieter (Ulfberg & Fenton, 1997).</p>",
